Rose "Osang" Fostanes (born January 2, 1967) is a Filipina caregiver and singer living in Israel, who on January 14, 2014, won the first season of The X Factor Israel On April 10, 2014, she signed a record contract with Star Records to release her music material in the Philippines.
Her debut album My Way was released on June 8, 2014.
Fostanes arrived in Israel in 2008 to work for an ailing woman in her 50s.
Fostanes auditioned for X Factor on October 26, 2013, singing the Shirley Bassey song, "This Is My Life".
On November 23, 2013, Fostanes performed at a charity event, "Concert for a Cause For Typhoon Yolanda" in Haifa, Israel, organized by the OFW in Israel Organization.
This was changed on January 20, 2014 when she was granted singing license in Israel.
Through her contract with Aroma Music, she performed during Israeli Independence Day shows in Acre and Tiberias.
She was awarded "Global Entertainer of the Year" at the Gawad Amerika Awards in Los Angeles.
On April 10, 2014, she signed a record contract with Star Records to release her music material in the Philippines.
Her Philippine debut album, My Way, was released on June 8.
In December 2015, Elijah Sparks released the single "Baby Love" that featured vocals by Rose Fostanes.
